+; MINIX userland links dynamic binaries by passing -dynamic through the
+; compiler driver. GCC 4.8 accepted this option, but GCC 13 no longer has
+; a generic definition for it, so the argument can leak into the final link
+; in the wrong shape. Keep recognizing it as a driver-only switch and let
+; minix-spec.h decide the actual link mode.
+
+dynamic
+Driver
